
Project Overview
This project aims to build an image captioning model. It will utilize a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for extracting features from images (encoder) and a Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) network for decoding these features into descriptive captions. The ultimate goal is that users will provide an input image, and the model will automatically generate a fitting caption for it.

Current Progress
1. Setup and Data Loading
Mounted Google Drive to access project files.
Loaded necessary libraries (tensorflow, numpy, pandas, matplotlib, etc.).
Defined DRIVE_PATH to locate the Images.zip and captions.txt files.
Extracted images from Images.zip to a temporary directory.
2. Caption Preprocessing
Loaded raw captions from captions.txt.
Implemented clean_text function to preprocess captions (lowercase, remove non-alphabetic characters, remove extra spaces).
Implemented map_image_to_captions to associate each image with its corresponding clean and tokenized captions (including startseq and endseq tokens).
Built a vocabulary from all captions, filtering out rare words (appearing less than 10 times).
Created word_to_idx and idx_to_word mappings for tokenization.
Determined the max_caption_length for padding sequences.
3. Image Feature Extraction (Encoder Setup)
Loaded a pre-trained InceptionV3 model (trained on ImageNet) for feature extraction.
Modified InceptionV3 by removing its final classification layer to obtain rich image features.
Defined preprocess_image function to prepare images for InceptionV3 input (resize, convert to array, expand dimensions, apply preprocess_input).
Next Steps
Extract features from all images using the model_inception.
Prepare data for model training (create sequences of captions, padding).
Define the CNN-LSTM model architecture.
Train the model.
Evaluate the model and generate captions for new images.

It's basically a chatbot
